item.description:
rv hijacking of dab page for an unsourced article

← Previous revision Revision as of 21:32, 20 July 2021
Line 1: Line 1:
'''Bhutani''' may refer to:
Its commonly used last name amongst Sindhi and Punjabi Hindus of erstwhile saptsindhu Pradesh or modern day sindh and Punjab. Originally part of Vedic Kshatriyas who took over to business post Islamic invasions.

Different variations have been found from bhutani to butani etc.
* [[Bhutani tribe]], a tribe of the Baloch people of Pakistan
* Bhutani language, a misnomer for several languages:
**[[Bhotia language]] or Sherpa language
**[[Bhutia language]] or Sikkimese language<!--https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=9bwgAAAAIAAJ&dq="bhutani"+dialect might not be the same as the one described in the target article-->
**[[Dzongkha]], the official language of Bhutan
**conceivably any [[Languages of Bhutan|language of Bhutan]]
**apparently also a certain dialect of the [[Balochi language]]
* [[Bhutanese people]], the people of Bhutan
* [[Bhutani Pony]], a breed of pony
